title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 §§ 14-10.8 - Tensile strength
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 §§ 14-10.8 - Tensile strength

State Regulations

When the tensile strength of steel or wrought-iron
shell plates is not known, it shall be taken at 55,000 pounds per square inch
for steel and 45,000 pounds for wrought iron. Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12
